Video Title: [3] Cara Membuat Deep Learning dengan Keras, TensorFlow Pada Python - Tutorial Indonesia
Description:
Mohon maaf pada video kali ini mic saya terlalu dekat, sehingga membuat suara pada video kurang jelas. Saya sarankan untuk tidak menggunakan headset dsb.
Pada video ini saya ingin berbagi sedikit pengalaman saya tentang bagaimana melakukan klasifikasi data penyakit diabetes menggunakan algoritma deep learning yang dibangun manual memanfaatkan keras dan tensorflow pada python 3. Hasil akurasi tentu saja belum maksimal dan masih dapat di optimasi melalui proses tuning hyperparameter, silahkan lakukan tuning secara mandiri dan share hasilnya di kolom komentar.

Video Title: Learn Neural Networks By Deriving And Coding One From Scratch In Python - Full Course (~2 hrs)
Description:
In this course, I explain the fundamentals of neural networks. I explain how they are derived and how they work. The course is motivated by a problem - building a machine to predict hand-written digits from the MNIST dataset. I start with a very simple linear binary classifier (the Perceptron) and with each lecture I improve the model until I have a Deep Neural Network.

All the code is written in Python and is hosted on GitHub (link below). I make use of NumPy and a tiny bit of Pandas and Matplotlib. No neural network libraries (e.g. TensorFlow and PyTorch) are used in this course, as it is about understanding fundamentals - not practical construction.

1:41:13 - 3.4 Multiclass Support
1:53:50 - 3.5 Deep Learning

2:08:13 - 3.7 Going Further

Video Title: Coder un réseau de neurones convolutifs de classification d'image avec Python et Tensorflow.
Description:
Les réseu de neurones convolutifs sont trés utilisés pour travailler sur les images. Une des applications classiques est la classification d'objet. C'est à dire montrer une image au réseau et lui laisser nous dire de quelle catégorie il s'agit. Le réseau aura appris en amont de centaines, de milliers voire de plusieurs millions d'image a reconnaitre les classes. 

Dans cette vidéo je vous montre la base pour construire un CNN, en construisant la base d'un pokedex (reconnaissance de pokemon) à vous de vous accaparer le code, construire vos jeux de données et en faire un projet personnel !

Le lien vers le notebook : https://github.com/anisayari/Youtube-apprendre-le-deeplearning-avec-tensorflow/blob/master/%234%20-%20CNN/A_deep_introduction_to_CNN%20(1).ipynb

L'extension pour les images : https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/image-downloader/cnpniohnfphhjihaiiggeabnkjhpaldj

Description:
[[1 HOUR]] End to End Guide on Pre-Trained Models & Transfer Learning | Advanced Deep Learning

Are you looking for a step by step guide on how to use pre-trained models and transfer learning for advanced deep learning? Then this video is for you!

In this 1 hour long video, we'll walk you through the entire process of using pre-trained models and transfer learning for deep learning. We'll cover topics like mobileNet, vgg16, and more.

This video is a must-watch if you want to start using pre-trained models and transfer learning for deep learning!

In this video, we will explore the benefits of pre-trained models and transfer learning in deep learning, and show you how to implement these techniques using a popular deep learning framework. We will cover the underlying theory and math behind these techniques, as well as practical considerations for data preparation, model training, and evaluation.

We will also share best practices and practical tips for working with pre-trained models and transferring learning, as well as examples of real-world applications that have leveraged these techniques to achieve impressive results.

Whether you're a beginner or an experienced deep learning practitioner, this video is a must-watch. By the end, you'll have a deep understanding of pre-trained models and transfer learning, as well as the tools and knowledge to apply them in your own deep learning projects.

Video Title: How to train machine learning agents to do fun and absurd things using Unity3D by A. Chatzizaharias
Description: While machine learning is often used for image recognition, speech recognition and the such, people tend to forget that there is another industry making full use of machine learning. The games industry. Within the games industry companies have been using machine learning to train their NPCs (non-player characters) a plethora of things. From basic combat behavior to full blown city building. During this session Alexander will show you what you can expect from using machine learning agents in Unity3D, an industry standard game engine. Alexander will demonstrate how to implement basic machine learning agents in Unity and how to train them! But the agents won't be trained to do standard stuff. From matrix bullet dodging to headbanging, we can train our agents to do the most absurd and fun things!

Video Title: CS25 I Stanford Seminar - Transformers United 2023: Introduction to Transformers w/ Andrej Karpathy
Description:
January 10, 2023
Introduction to Transformers
Andrej Karpathy: https://karpathy.ai/

Since their introduction in 2017, transformers have revolutionized Natural Language Processing (NLP). Now, transformers are finding applications all over Deep Learning, be it computer vision (CV), reinforcement learning (RL), Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), Speech or even Biology. Among other things, transformers have enabled the creation of powerful language models like GPT-3 and were instrumental in DeepMind's recent AlphaFold2, that tackles protein folding.

In this speaker series, we examine the details of how transformers work, and dive deep into the different kinds of transformers and how they're applied in different fields. We do this by inviting people at the forefront of transformers research across different domains for guest lectures. 

More about the course can be found here: https://web.stanford.edu/class/cs25/

Video Title: INTELIGENCIA ARTIFICIAL en PYTHON | Qué es? 💡 Cómo aprende? 😵 Cómo se programa? 😱
Description:
👉 ¿Sabes qué es la Inteligencia Artificial 🤖 en qué consiste, cómo aprenden las máquinas o cómo programarla?

En este vídeo programamos una Inteligencia Artificial (IA) en Python utilizando los algoritmos Q-Learning y Deep-Q-Network. Haremos uso de Redes Neuronales para que la IA aprenda a jugar automáticamente a un juego de coches hecho en PyGame. Te lo vas a perder? ;)

📝 Í N D I C E
00:00 Introducción
0:16 Exploración del juego original
1:08 Qué es el RL
2:34 Entrenamiento de la IA
3:23 Revisión del código
9:45 Despedida, suscripción y like

La IA:
La inteligencia artificial (IA) es la inteligencia llevada a cabo por máquinas. En ciencias de la computación, una máquina «inteligente» ideal es un agente flexible que percibe su entorno y lleva a cabo acciones que maximicen sus posibilidades de éxito en algún objetivo o tarea. Coloquialmente, el término inteligencia artificial se aplica cuando una máquina imita las funciones «cognitivas» que los humanos asocian con otras mentes humanas, como por ejemplo: «percibir», «razonar», «aprender» y «resolver problemas».

Video Title: Feature engineering in Machine learning | A step by Step Guide | in Urdu/Hindi
Description:
#datascience 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Video Description:
Unlock the secrets of successful Machine Learning with our comprehensive guide on Feature Engineering! This tutorial is a deep dive into the art and science of preparing your data to boost the performance of your models.

Whether you're a beginner or an experienced data scientist, this video will equip you with the skills to transform raw data into a goldmine of insights. We'll explore techniques like normalization, binning, encoding, feature selection, and much more.

Don't let unoptimized data hold back your machine learning projects. Get ready to elevate your data preprocessing game and make your machine learning models more accurate than ever!


Remember to Like, Share, and Subscribe for more tutorials on Machine Learning and Data Science!

#FeatureEngineering #MachineLearning #DataScience #DataPreprocessing #Python
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Feature engineering is the process of creating new input features for machine learning. Each input feature is a column of data that the machine learning model uses to make its predictions or classifications. Feature engineering makes a machine learning model more accurate by providing it with more or better input, making it one of the most important steps in building an effective model.

The major steps involved in feature engineering are typically:

Brainstorming or Testing Features: The first step is to consider what features could potentially improve the performance of your model. This might be based on your understanding of the problem, domain knowledge, or previous experiences.

Creating Features: Once you have an idea of what features to create, the next step is to create them. This could involve anything from simple arithmetic operations to complex calculations.

Checking how the Features work with your Model: After creating features, the next step is to include them in your model and see how they affect its performance. If a feature improves your model, you'll want to keep it. If not, you can discard it.

Iterating on your Features: After testing your features, you might have new ideas for features to create. Alternatively, you might find that slight tweaks to your features improve their performance. Thus, this process is often iterative.

Video Title: Introduction to PyTorch and Deep Learning I - Machine Learning Basics - Lecture
Description:
Welcome to the Introduction to PyTorch and Deep Learning online class, which will teach you some basic topics in machine learning.

The course begins with an overview of what machine learning is, how it differs from traditional programming, and the different types of machine learning. We will then examine some examples of modern machine-learning applications, including image recognition, speech recognition, and natural language processing.

Afterward, we dive into linear regression, which is a fundamental machine-learning technique for predicting a continuous output variable based on one or more input variables. We will cover the basic concepts of linear regression, including the cost function, gradient descent, and regularization.

We also cover the concepts of bias and variance and how they can impact the accuracy of machine-learning models.

Finally, we will introduce maximum likelihood, a powerful statistical technique used to estimate the parameters of a model by maximizing the likelihood of observing the data. We will show how maximum likelihood can be used to estimate the parameters of linear regression models and other types of machine learning models.

Video Title: Web Development,Graphic Designing,Artificial Intelligence,Machine Learning,Python Programming
Description:
To receive text input in Python, you can use the `input()` function. The `input()` function allows you to prompt the user for input and returns the text entered by the user as a string.

Here's a simple example:

```python
name = input("Enter your name: ")
print("Hello, " + name + "!")
```

In this example, the program prompts the user to enter their name. The `input()` function takes a string argument that represents the prompt. The user can then type their name and press enter. The entered text is stored in the `name` variable, which can be used later in the program.

The program then prints a greeting message using the entered name.

When you run this code, it will display the prompt, wait for the user to enter text, and then print the greeting message.

Keep in mind that the `input()` function always returns a string, so if you want to perform numerical operations with the input, you may need to convert it to the appropriate data type using functions like `int()` or `float()`.

The Growing availability of data has made way for Data Science and Machine Learning to become in-demand professions. We define Statistics for Data Science - Predictive Analytics as exposure to Statistics which is essential for anyone seeking a career in Data Science and Machine learning. In this course, you will get the required college math , statistics and its practical implementation from Data Analytics which are necessary to better understand what goes in the black box libraries(sklearn) that you would encounter in the Data Science Journey.

With this course, as a learner, you will be exposed to various Statistics and Machine Learning topics that will apply to real-world problems.

The Ultimate goal of taking this structured approach is to integrate everything we learn and demonstrate practical insights in using Machine learning and Statistical Libraries beyond a black-box understanding.

Why Learn from Us ??

Description:
Hi, thanks for watching our video about Elon Musk Tesla Humanoid AI robot called Optimus. 

Tesla is showing off how well its Optimus robots can walk in a new video showcasing their movements. The video highlights advances made in the nearly two years since CEO Elon Musk vowed to create the humanoid robots and brought a human in a robot suit onstage to kick off the project.


Tesla shared a video of its humanoid bot this week that shows the bounds it has made (literally) since the first shaky prototype was revealed at the marque’s AI day last year.

OpenAI has officially announced GPT-4  the latest version of its incredibly popular large language model powering artificial intelligence (AI) chatbots. ChatGPT is an AI chatbot that utilizes the language models of GPT-3 and GPT-4 for interactive communication.  In other words you can use chatgpt with gpt4.  A Generative Pre-Trained Transformer (GPT) is a sophisticated neural network architecture used to train large language models (LLMs). It makes use of large amounts of publicly available Internet text to simulate human communication.

Main improvements:
* It's multimodal (what it is is in video)
* Longer context length 
* Better performance 
* More safer

ZTECH LEARNING offers a variety of courses related to web designing, web development, graphic designing, artificial intelligence, machine learning, digital marketing, social media marketing, and more. Here's a brief description of some of the courses offered:

Web Designing: This course covers the principles of designing user-friendly and visually appealing websites. Students learn HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, which are essential skills for creating responsive web pages.

Web Development: This course teaches students how to create dynamic and interactive web applications using various programming languages such as PHP, Python, and JavaScript.

Graphic Designing: In this course, students learn how to create visually appealing designs for logos, brochures, flyers, posters, and more using software like Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator, and InDesign.

Artificial Intelligence: This course introduces students to the basics of artificial intelligence, including machine learning, deep learning, natural language processing, and computer vision.

Machine Learning: This course covers the fundamentals of machine learning algorithms and their applications. Students learn how to build predictive models using Python, TensorFlow, and other popular libraries.

Digital Marketing: This course teaches students how to use various digital marketing tools and techniques to promote products and services online. Topics covered include SEO, PPC, email marketing, and social media marketing.

Social Media Marketing: This course focuses on leveraging social media platforms such as Facebook, Twitter, LinkedIn, and Instagram to promote brands and engage with customers.

Java: ZTECH LEARNING offers Java courses for beginners and advanced learners. These courses cover topics such as Java syntax, object-oriented programming, data structures, algorithms, and more.

C and C++: ZTECH LEARNING offers C and C++ courses for beginners and intermediate learners. These courses cover topics such as C and C++ syntax, data types, control flow, functions, pointers, and more.

MERN stack: ZTECH LEARNING provides courses on the MERN (MongoDB, Express, React, Node.js) stack for web development. These courses cover topics such as setting up a MERN stack, building RESTful APIs, creating user interfaces with React, and more.

MySQL: ZTECH LEARNING offers MySQL courses for beginners and intermediate learners. These courses cover topics such as SQL syntax, data manipulation, data modeling, database design, and more.

PHP: ZTECH LEARNING provides PHP courses for beginners and intermediate learners. These courses cover topics such as PHP syntax, data types, control flow, functions, arrays, and more.

HTML and CSS: ZTECH LEARNING offers courses on HTML and CSS for beginners and intermediate learners. These courses cover topics such as HTML and CSS syntax, creating web pages and layouts, styling web pages, and more.

React JS: ZTECH LEARNING provides courses on React JS for beginners and intermediate learners. These courses cover topics such as React syntax, component-based architecture, managing state and props, and more.

Python: ZTECH LEARNING provides Python courses for beginners and intermediate learners. These courses cover topics such as Python basics, data types, control flow, functions, modules, and more.

The course covers a wide range of topics, including Python syntax, data types, control structures, functions, modules, and more. The curriculum also includes real-world projects and assignments that allow learners to apply their knowledge and skills to practical scenarios.

ZTECH Learning's Python course includes interactive video lessons, coding exercises, quizzes, and a supportive community of learners and instructors. The course is self-paced, which means that learners can study at their own pace and on their own schedule.

Upon completing the course, learners will have a solid foundation in Python programming and be able to create their own Python programs and applications. They will also receive a certificate of completion to showcase their achievement.

Overall, ZTECH Learning's Python programming course is a great option for anyone looking to learn Python programming in a structured and supportive environment.



In addition to these courses, ZTECH LEARNING offers a range of other courses related to cybersecurity, blockchain technology, data science, and more. All courses are designed to provide students with the practical skills and knowledge needed to succeed in today's digital world.

Video Title: Advantages and Disadvantages of ChatGPT
Description:
Benefits of ChatGPT:
Versatility: ChatGPT is a flexible language model that can participate in a variety of conversational tasks, making it appropriate for a wide range of applications.
Natural language processing: It can comprehend and produce text that sounds like human speech, making conversations with it more interesting and natural.
Knowledge and information: ChatGPT has access to a wealth of knowledge, enabling it to offer solutions, justifications, and recommendations based on its pre-trained expertise.
Capabilities for learning: It can be tailored for certain activities or domains, enabling superior performance in niche circumstances.
24/7 accessibility: ChatGPT is always available, offering regular and dependable support.
Negative aspects of ChatGPT:Lack of real-world awareness: It relies on patterns and correlations in training data and lacks a realistic grasp of the world, which might result in inaccurate or absurd responses.Consistent replies: The model appears inconsistent because even little variations in the query's wording or order might provide noticeably different responses.ChatGPT is quite sensitive to the way questions are framed, so users must experiment with rephrasing in order to get the desired results.Bias propagation: Due to biases contained in the training data, it may unintentionally provide biassed or discriminatory replies.Cutoff for limited knowledge: Since ChatGPT's training data only extends until September 2021, it can be unaware of current affairs or advancements.Ethical considerations: To address potential problems, responsible use and protections are required.

DragGAN: An AI Based Image Editing Tool
Description:
Drag Your GAN is a new ai bases image editing tool. It allows users to manipulate images by dragging points on the image. The tool is based on a generative adversarial network (GAN). GAN is a type of machine learning model. It can generate realistic images. Drag Your GAN uses the GAN to create a new image. This image is based on the original image. It incorporates the changes that the user has made. It can replace Photoshop in near future. I'm so excited to try this out!

Video Title: Full lộ trình tự học Data Science
Description:
Trong video này mình sẽ chia sẻ với các bạn lộ trình tự học Data Science hoàn toàn miễn phí

Mình tên là Việt. Hiện tại mình đang sinh sống và làm việc tại Berlin, Đức. Mình là Senior AI engineer (kĩ sư trí tuệ nhân tạo). Công ty của mình hoạt động về lĩnh vực thể thao, cụ thể là sport streaming. Mình tốt nghiệp đại học ngành CNTT tại đại học Bách Khoa Hà Nội, rồi sau đó mình học tiếp lên thạc sĩ tại đại học kĩ thuật Munich, chuyên ngành trí tuệ nhân tạo và robot. Mình đã làm việc trong lĩnh vực AI được 7 năm rồi. Mình mong rằng qua kênh youtube này, mình có thể chia sẽ với các bạn kinh nghiệm cũng như kiến thức về CNTT nói chung cũng như AI nói riêng.

Hiện tại mình đang mở các khóa học:
- Data Science/Machine Learning/Python cơ bản
- Data Science/Machine Learning/Python nâng cao
- Deep Learning for Computer Vision

Nếu các bạn quan tâm tới các khóa học của mình, các bạn có thể liên hệ với mình để biết thêm thông tin chi tiết

Video Title: 5G Throughput Simulation with Python - By Ali
Description:
5G Throughput Simulation with Python - By Ali
Python (Session 2): Practical 5G Throughput Simulation with Python

In the previous session, we developed a basic 5G Interactive Throughput Calculator that takes some inputs from the user and generates the peak throughput for the given configuration. However, this approach cannot be used for general purposes as most of the users will be in different radio conditions and hence, they will get different throughput levels. So, in this session, we will convert that basic 5G Tool into a more practical version which will be able to provide throughput for 5G Users in various radio conditions. This means that we will add more input parameters including MCS (Modulation and Coding Scheme), CQI (Channel Quality Indicator) and BLER (Block Error Rate). Meanwhile, we will also increase our knowledge of Python as we will introduce the concept of Python Lists, improving the interaction by creating choice and learning about IF and IF-ELSE statements. So, do have a look as I have tried to cover both 5G and Python simultaneously!

The MCS and CQI tables discussed in the session are given below. You can copy them from here and use them in your own test code!

 Throughout this section, we'll take a step-by-step approach, carefully explaining each line of code, ensuring you have a solid understanding of Kafka concepts and how they relate to Python. But before we jump into the code, let's talk about why Kafka and Python make a great combination.
Kafka, a distributed streaming platform, has gained immense popularity for its ability to handle large-scale, real-time data processing. Python, being a versatile and widely adopted programming language, provides an excellent ecosystem for developing Kafka applications.

In this section, we'll work with the latest version of Kafka (version 3 or above), ensuring that you're up to date with the latest features and improvements. This hands-on approach will equip you with the skills needed to confidently work with Kafka in real-world scenarios.

Video Title: Python For 4G and 5G Throughput Calculations - By Ali
Description:
Practical Python Use Cases (Session 1):
How To Create Basic 5G Interactive Tools

Practical Python Use Cases (Session 1): How To Create
Basic 5G Interactive Tools
The idea about these Python sessions is to start from the basics and beginner level and discuss how we can use Python to perform various calculations, simulations and automations related to Telecom technologies like 4G, LTE, VOLTE and 5G.
This is the first session of the series and it starts with a basic Python code that takes input from the user. Then it explains how multiple different operations can be performed on this input. Thus, the audience will be able to create interactive applications or programs based on this session.
Then, in the end, we discover how we can use this python knowledge to make a simple 5G speed or throughput calculator which takes input from the user about the 5G configuration (like Bandwidth of the channel, number of MIMO layers) and gives the maximum achievable 5G throughput or speed as an output.
